      "writtenOn": "2019-01-27T03:27:02Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "So.. this is a state machine that consumes tokens from the tokenizer, just like taught in serious compiler books.\n\nEverything is pretty dumb, but verbose. I tried to adhoc this, but there are too many edge cases related to handling of escaping (e.g. \u0027{{\u0027). State machine + tokenizer approach is solid, it covers all scenarios by construction.\n\nNote that the grammar here is significantly more powerful as used in Swarming itself. Swarming only allows {1,2,3} or {1-3}, but not both at the same time. And it doesn\u0027t support escaping \u0027{\u0027, and it doesn\u0027t support padding with zeros.\n\nI did it because I\u0027ve noticed the syntax used by Swarming is lacking, e.g. https://chrome-internal.googlesource.com/infradata/config/+/9c907e937cb82690843a99fa29ad578218718ff0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 26,
        "startChar": 5,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "c4d4432bc72a6efd9e3861827b8f7855e57ecf7a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
